====Definitions====
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# to [[govern]]; to [[regulate]]; to [[administer]]
#: {{zh-co|治國|to govern a state}}
# to [[treat]]; to [[cure]] (disease)
#: {{zh-co|治病|to treat an illness}}
# to [[harness]]; to [[control]] {{gl|a river, etc.}}
#: {{zh-co|治水|to control water resources to prevent flooding}}
# to [[exterminate]]; to [[kill]]
#: {{zh-co|治蝗|to eliminate locusts}}
# to [[punish]]; to [[penalize]]
#: {{zh-co|治罪|to punish (a criminal, wrongdoer, etc.)}}
# to [[research]]; to [[specialise]] in (a topic)
#: {{zh-co|治學|to do scholarly research}}
# [[orderly]]; [[peaceful]]; [[socially]] [[stable]]
#: {{zh-co|大治|(of a country) orderly and prosperous}}
# to [[manage]]; to [[operate]]; to [[run]]
#: {{zh-co|治產|to manage property}}
# to [[teach]] someone a [[lesson]]; to [[discipline]]; to [[make]] someone [[endure]] [[hardship]] to [[pay]] for his [[action]]s
#: {{zh-x|哎-呦{you}！可 有人 治-治{zhi} 這.個 賤貨 了！|Ah! Finally there is someone to '''teach''' this nasty person '''a lesson'''!}}
